<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Joe Napalm:
[B]
I had thought that you could wear greaves over other armor...like boots. You can wear leather leggings and studded leather boots, even though both cover the lower legs.

Of course, I haven't tried it...I just figured it worked that way or all of those studded leather greaves would be useless...

Hmmm.

Horses, while cool, I don't think are gonna make it. Too many issues, too little "value added" (don't you hate buzz words?)...Besides, people can already run faster than the servers can track, so what good are horses going to be?

Different denominations of pyreal don't really make much sense. Trade notes cover most of your money needs, and most people don't bother with anything smaller than a 1k note. Adding 5, 25, and 100 pyreal coins would just needlessly clutter up your inventory until you could get to a shop to buy a nice, light trade note.

My only thought on the "docks" is - How do you explain having multiple versions of Dereth, which people can travel between? It doesn't make much sense in terms of the story.

-Jn-[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
